For comparison, the current price cap stands at £1,971 and is set to hit £3,582 in October. A year ago the cap was £1,138.The collective debt is now three times higher than 12 months ago - with six million homes an average £206 in the red. And forecasts jumped yet again yesterday - with analysts Cornwall Insight predicting a leap to £4,266 in January, then £4,427 in April. Last week Investec said it expects January's price cap to be £4,210.